  ('Bird Dog ISO Hold', 'bird-dog-iso-hold', 'Start on hands and knees, reach opposite arm and leg, and hold a long line without shifting the pelvis.', 'BEGINNER', 8, 2, NULL, 30, 30, 70, 'Contralateral trunk-control drill that teaches the athlete to resist rotation and extension while reaching opposite limbs.', 'Primary subrole: Trunk / Pelvis Anti-Movement Control. Coach Bird Dog ISO Hold as quality-first Core & Body Control work: clean setup, steady breath, controlled range, and immediate stop when position leaks.', 'Reach long; hips stay square; breathe.', 'Quadruped / Crawling Shoulder-Core Control', 'resilience', 'trunk_pelvis_anti_movement_control', 'contralateral_trunk_control', '{"primary_joint_actions":["spine_anti_rotation","shoulder_flexion","hip_extension"],"primary_tissues":["abdominals","glutes","spinal_erectors","serratus_anterior"],"primary_motor_control_demands":[],"postural_shape":null,"breathing_demand":"controlled_bracing","balance_demand":"stable","coordination_demand":"low","impact_level":0}'::jsonb, '{"movement_description":"Start on hands and knees, reach opposite arm and leg, and hold a long line without shifting the pelvis.","setup":["Clear the floor or training lane and choose the easiest variation the athlete can control.","Start on hands and knees, reach opposite arm and leg, and hold a long line without shifting the pelvis.","Set ribs over pelvis, establish quiet breathing, and define the stop rule before the first rep."],"execution_steps":["Begin Bird Dog ISO Hold from the coached start position.","Move slowly enough that the trunk, pelvis, shoulder, and hip positions remain organized.","Breathe behind the brace instead of holding air or grinding.","Pause briefly at the hardest point, then return under control.","Stop the set when the athlete cannot repeat the same position."],"coach_cues":["Ribs over pelvis.","Breathe behind the brace.","Move only through the range you own.","Quiet hips, quiet ribs.","Stop before the position changes