  ('Medicine Ball Rotational Catch-and-Stick', 'medicine-ball-rotational-catch-and-stick', 'Partner tosses a light medicine ball from the side; the athlete catches, rotates only as planned, and freezes under control.', 'BEGINNER', 8, 2, 4, 30, 45, 70, 'Low-amplitude partner catch drill that teaches the athlete to receive rotation and stick a controlled trunk position.', 'Primary subrole: Perception-Action Reactive Movement. Coach Medicine Ball Rotational Catch-and-Stick as quality-first Core & Body Control work: clean setup, steady breath, controlled range, and immediate stop when position leaks.', 'Catch soft, rotate under control, stick the finish.', 'Anti-Rotation / Rotational Trunk Control', 'movement_intelligence', 'perception_action_reactive_movement', 'rotational_catch_stick_control', '{"primary_joint_actions":["spine_rotation_control","deceleration_catch","hip_pelvis_control"],"primary_tissues":["obliques","abdominals","glutes","forearms"],"primary_motor_control_demands":[],"postural_shape":null,"breathing_demand":"controlled_bracing","balance_demand":"moderate","coordination_demand":"high","impact_level":1}'::jsonb, '{"movement_description":"Partner tosses a light medicine ball from the side; the athlete catches, rotates only as planned, and freezes under control.","setup":["Clear the floor or training lane and choose the easiest variation the athlete can control.","Partner tosses a light medicine ball from the side; the athlete catches, rotates only as planned, and freezes under control.","Set ribs over pelvis, establish quiet breathing, and define the stop rule before the first rep."],"execution_steps":["Begin Medicine Ball Rotational Catch-and-Stick from the coached start position.","Move slowly enough that the trunk, pelvis, shoulder, and hip positions remain organized.","Breathe behind the brace instead of holding air or grinding.","Pause briefly at the hardest point, then return under control.","Stop the set when the athlete cannot repeat the same pos